    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3476292989" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3476292989" />
    <a title="Hanneke" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17944903-hanneke"><img alt="Hanneke" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1546964664p2/17944903.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3476292989?book_show_action=true">Feb 07, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hanneke" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hanneke" href="/user/show/17944903-hanneke">Hanneke</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780099526698" href="/book/show/50619142-the-information">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3476292989" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11534947456602773419">I know it’s rather strange to present my appreciation of The Information like this, but if I could use a scale which explains my feeling as to the level of Martin Amis’ (usually very enjoyable) cynicism (at 1) to downright viciousness (at 10), I would classify the content of the novel in general at around 7 or 8 with lots of peaks to 9 and quite often a downright lash to 10. <br/>There is no doubt in my mind that Martin Amis is one of the rare authors worldwide who is able to write a truly toxic nove</span>
  <span id="freeText11534947456602773419" style="display:none">I know it’s rather strange to present my appreciation of The Information like this, but if I could use a scale which explains my feeling as to the level of Martin Amis’ (usually very enjoyable) cynicism (at 1) to downright viciousness (at 10), I would classify the content of the novel in general at around 7 or 8 with lots of peaks to 9 and quite often a downright lash to 10. <br />There is no doubt in my mind that Martin Amis is one of the rare authors worldwide who is able to write a truly toxic novel. Houellebecq, eat your heart out! I must confess it was hard to read those marvelous sentences in this novel containing all that clever abuse and not give up. However, my admiration for Amis’ great writing, however nasty it was, won it time and again over my feelings of disgust and I continued with great effort to the end at page 494, uttering a huge sign of relief.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11534947456602773419" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


